A UNIVERSITY CLUB IN HONOLULU. On December 17, the first university club meeting was held at H,onolulu, Hawaiian Islands. President Dole, 'Chief Justice Judd, and Justices Frear and Whiting were the guests of honor. Graduates of Harvard, Williams, Cornell, Yale, Oberlin, Amherst, Columbia, W esieyan, Dartmouth, Brown and other American colleges were present. Chief Justice Judd, the president of the club, introduced A. L. Colston, C. E., Cornell, who spoke on the relative merits of scientifi.c and classical institu- tions. Several of the speakers discussed this question. Toasts to the various colleges were responded to by graduates, college songs were sung, and a university club was very pleasantly inaugurated in the far away islands whose name is .of sucl1 interest to Americans at home.- Cor- nell Da-ily' Sun.
